{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C. Spray a loaf tin (27 x 10 x 7cm) and baking tray (30 x 40 cm) with oil and set aside.","Place onion, parsley and bread into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>.","Add nutmeg, milk, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, 20 g of the tomato sauce, egg, salt and pepper and combine <b>30 sec\/speed 2<b>. Transfer into a large bowl and add mince. Stir well to combine with aid of spatula.","Transfer mixture into prepared loaf tin and press down firmly. Place loaf tin upside down onto prepared baking tray  and bake for 30 minutes (180°C), leaving loaf tin in place to hold shape of meatloaf. Rinse mixing bowl. Continue with recipe while meatloaf is in the oven.","Place mustard powder, brown sugar and remaining tomato sauce into mixing bowl and cook <b>7 min\/100°C\/speed 2<b>. Transfer into a bowl. Rinse mixing bowl.","Place water into mixing bowl. Place Varoma dish into position and weigh potatoes into it. Secure Varoma lid and steam <b>40 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Meanwhile, after meatloaf has cooked for 30 minutes, carefully remove loaf tin from meatloaf and baste with three-quarters of the reserved tomato sauce mixture. Bake for a further 20 minutes (without tin).","Carefully transfer steamed potatoes onto baking tray next to the meatloaf, cover with meat juices, and continue to cook meatloaf for 20-30 minutes, until juices run clear. Serve meatloaf and potatoes with vegetables of choice."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["olive oil spray, for greasing","1 brown onion, cut into halves","10 sprigs fresh flat-leaf parsley, cut into thirds","3 slices day old bread, torn into pieces","1 tsp nutmeg","250 g milk","2 tsp Dijon mustard","1 ½ tbsp Worcestershire sauce","260 g tomato sauce (see Tip)","1 egg","½ tsp salt","½ tsp ground black pepper","1000 g beef mince","2 - 3 tsp mustard powder, to taste","2 tbsp brown sugar","1000 g water","18 - 20 new baby potatoes (2-3 per serve), washed"]}],"id":"